# serialized and trasmitted objects in YARP are called IDL
# these objects are declared into a trift file, and code is automatically
# generated to create classes out of it for c++ etc
# http://www.yarp.it/thrift_editor.html

# $ yarp server (t1)
# $ yarp cmake && cmake . && make && ./yarpy (build and run in t2)
# $ echo "1 sam (1 2 3)" | yarp write /write /settings  (t3)
#         or (with Editor in settings)
# $ echo 'set name "sam"' | yarp write /write /settings (t3)
#         or (commands via RPC, one by one ... )
# $ yarp rpc /settings (t3)
# $ >> set id 12
# $ >> set name tony
# $ >> set ints (8 9 10 11)

